/*
Function Templates

    To see template functions generated in the assembly file from C++ code

    step 1:

    compile the code into assembly with verbose annotations:

    g++ -S -fverbose-asm -g -o output.s main.cpp

    mixed view of the C++ source and the assembly:

    g++ -g -c -Wa,-adhln -fverbose-asm main.cpp > output.s

    ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
    step 2:

    Identifying Template Instantiations
    In the assembly file:

    Look for functions with mangled names. These correspond to template instantiations.
    Use c++filt to demangle names for better readability.

    _Z3addIiET_S0_S0_:     # Template instantiated for int
    _Z3addIdET_S0_S0_:     # Template instantiated for double

    To demangle:

    $c++filt _Z3addIiET_S0_S0_

    output:
    add<int>(int, int)

*/